  "text": "When the queries and views are expressed as conjunctive queries (without arithmetic comparisons), we know how to find equivalent rewritings (if they exist) and maximally-contained rewritings (MCRs) that are unions of conjunctive queries (see [CITATION_1] for a survey). However, arithmetic comparisons introduce many complications to the problem. In particular, both the containment mapping theorem [CITATION_2] and the theorem for unions of CQs [CITATION_3] no longer hold.",
